You are a senior full‑stack engineer. Generate a COMPLETE, production‑ready, fully dynamic website with an Admin Panel CMS using PHP 8+ and MySQL (PDO). Use an MVC structure and RESTful APIs.

# Core Features (must-have)
1) Admin Authentication
- Secure login/logout
- Password hashing using password_hash() + password_verify()
- Session-based auth with secure cookie settings
- CSRF protection on all state-changing requests (forms + API)
- Rate limit login attempts (basic IP/session throttle)
- Auth middleware for all /admin and /api/admin routes

2) Dynamic Content Management (CRUD)
Admin can create/update/delete:
- Pages (title, slug, SEO meta, status, publish date)
- Sections (page_id, type, sort_order, visibility)
- Content blocks (text, rich text, image, gallery, video embed, CTA, FAQ)
- Media library (images/videos/files) with upload + storage path + alt text
- Menus/navigation (optional but preferred)

3) Dynamic Frontend Rendering
- Public site routes render pages by slug from DB
- Page builder style: each page loads its ordered sections/blocks dynamically
- Clean, responsive UI (mobile-first)
- Semantic HTML + accessibility (labels, focus states, skip links)
- Consistent typography and card-based components

4) Admin Dashboard
- Summary cards: total pages, total sections, total media, total users/admins
- Recent activity feed: latest edits/creates/deletes
- Tables must be mobile-friendly (stacked rows or horizontal scroll)
- Search/filter for pages and content

5) REST API (JSON)
Implement REST endpoints (examples; add more as needed):
- POST   /api/admin/auth/login
- POST   /api/admin/auth/logout
- GET    /api/admin/dashboard
- GET    /api/admin/pages
- POST   /api/admin/pages
- GET    /api/admin/pages/{id}
- PUT    /api/admin/pages/{id}
- DELETE /api/admin/pages/{id}
- GET/POST/PUT/DELETE for sections and blocks
- POST   /api/admin/media (multipart upload)
- GET    /api/admin/media
All responses must be JSON with consistent error format, HTTP status codes, and validation errors.

# Database Requirements
Provide a MySQL schema + seed data. Include at minimum:
- admins (id, name, email unique, password_hash, role, is_active, last_login_at, timestamps)
- pages (id, title, slug unique, meta_title, meta_description, status, published_at, timestamps)
- sections (id, page_id, type, sort_order, is_active, settings_json, timestamps)
- blocks (id, section_id, type, sort_order, content_json, timestamps)
- media (id, file_path, mime_type, size, alt_text, title, uploaded_by_admin_id, timestamps)
- audit_logs (id, admin_id, entity_type, entity_id, action, diff_json, ip, user_agent, created_at)

# Admin UI Requirements
- Modern responsive layout using CSS Grid/Flexbox
- Reusable components: sidebar/topbar, cards, table, modal/dialog, toast alerts
- Theme support (light/dark via CSS variables)
- Subtle animations (respect prefers-reduced-motion)
- Clear empty states and loading states

# Security Requirements
- Input validation + output escaping
- Prepared statements everywhere
- File upload validation (size/mime/extension), random filenames, prevent executing uploads
- Store uploads outside public when possible OR protect with .htaccess rules
- Prevent XSS in rich text (sanitize allowlist OR store as plain text)
- Proper authorization checks for each action

# Optional (nice-to-have)
- Role-based permissions (super_admin/editor)
- Real-time updates for dashboard/activity (SSE or polling)
- Content versioning + rollback
- Slug auto-generation + uniqueness enforcement

